# Fresh Search

Web search optimized for AI agents with high-quality, up-to-date results.

## Overview

`fresh search` provides intelligent web search powered by Exa.ai. It offers multiple search types from fast keyword matching to deep reasoning synthesis, with results optimized for AI consumption.

## CLI Usage

```bash
fresh search <query> [options]
```

### Arguments

| Argument | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `query` | Search query string (required) |

### Options

| Flag | Description | Default |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `--type <type>` | Search type: `auto`, `fast`, `deep-lite`, `deep`, `deep-reasoning`, `instant` | `auto` |
| `--num-results <n>` | Number of results to return | `10` |
| `--highlight-query <q>` | Query for extracting relevant highlights | - |
| `--text-max <n>` | Maximum characters for text content per result | `1000` |
| `--format <type>` | Output format: `json`, `markdown`, `text` | `json` |

### Search Types

| Type | Description | Best For |
|------|-------------|----------|
| `auto` | Automatically selects best search mode | General use |
| `fast` | Quick keyword-based search | Speed-critical |
| `deep-lite` | Light semantic search | Quick insights |
| `deep` | Deep semantic understanding | Comprehensive research |
| `deep-reasoning` | Multi-step reasoning synthesis | Complex analysis |
| `instant` | Instant answer mode | Quick facts |

### Examples

```bash
# Basic search
fresh search "hottest AI startups 2024"

# Deep research search
fresh search "impact of AI on healthcare" --type deep --num-results 20

# Fast search with highlights
fresh search "latest React framework" --type fast --highlight-query "performance"
```

## API Usage

### Exa.search

Performs a web search with configurable depth.

**Endpoint:** `POST /api/search`

**Input Parameters:**

| Parameter | Type | Description | Default |
|-----------|------|-------------|---------|
| `query` | `string` | Search query | Required |
| `options.type` | `string` | Search type: `auto`, `fast`, `deep-lite`, `deep`, `deep-reasoning`, `instant` | `auto` |
| `options.numResults` | `number` | Number of results | `10` |
| `options.highlights.query` | `string` | Query for relevant highlights | - |
| `options.highlights.maxCharacters` | `number` | Max highlight length | `200` |
| `options.text.maxCharacters` | `number` | Max text length per result | `1000` |
| `options.contents` | `object` | Content extraction options | - |

### Request Example

```json
{
  "query": "hottest AI startups",
  "options": {
    "type": "auto",
    "numResults": 10,
    "highlights": {
      "query": "AI funding valuation",
      "maxCharacters": 200
    },
    "text": {
      "maxCharacters": 1000
    }
  }
}
```

### Response Example

```json
{
  "autopromptString": "Here is a link to one of the hottest AI startups:",
  "results": [
    {
      "title": "Adept: Useful General Intelligence",
      "id": "https://www.adept.ai/",
      "url": "https://www.adept.ai/",
      "publishedDate": "2024-03-15",
      "author": null,
      "text": "Adept is building AI that can automate any software process..."
    }
  ],
  "requestId": "a78ebce717f4d712b6f8fe0d5d7753f8",
  "costDollars": {
    "stDollars": 0.001,
    "totalCost": 0.001
  },
  "statuses": [
    {
      "code": "success",
      "url": "https://www.adept.ai/"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Result Object

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `results` | `SearchResult[]` | List of search results |
| `results[].title` | `string` | Result title |
| `results[].id` | `string` | Unique identifier (mirrors URL) |
| `results[].url` | `string` | Source URL |
| `results[].publishedDate` | `string` | Publication date (ISO 8601) |
| `results[].author` | `string \| null` | Author name |
| `results[].text` | `string` | Extracted text content |
| `autopromptString` | `string` | AI-friendly prompt prefix |
| `requestId` | `string` | Request ID for debugging |
| `costDollars.stDollars` | `number` | Soft dollar cost |
| `costDollars.totalCost` | `number` | Total cost in dollars |

### Deep Reasoning Output

When using `--type deep-reasoning`, the response includes an `output` field:

```json
{
  "output": {
    "content": "Synthesized analysis based on multiple sources...",
    "grounding": [
      {
        "field": "statistics",
        "citations": [
          { "url": "https://example.com/source", "title": "Source Title" }
        ],
        "confidence": "high"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

## Features

### Search Modes

- **Auto mode** - Exa automatically selects optimal search strategy
- **Fast mode** - Quick keyword matching for speed
- **Deep modes** - Semantic understanding with varying depth
- **Deep reasoning** - Multi-step analysis with synthesized output

### Content Extraction

- **Highlight extraction** - Query-relevant passage extraction
- **Text snippets** - Clean, truncated content per result
- **Metadata** - Publication dates, authors, categories

### AI Optimization

- **Autoprompt string** - Ready-to-use prompt prefix for LLMs
- **Grounded citations** - Source attribution for facts
- **Confidence levels** - Low, medium, high per grounding

## Error Handling

### Error Response

```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "SEARCH_ERROR",
    "message": "Search failed",
    "details": "Rate limit exceeded"
  }
}
```

### Error Codes

| Code | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `INVALID_QUERY` | Query is empty or invalid |
| `SEARCH_ERROR` | Search operation failed |
| `TIMEOUT` | Search exceeded timeout |
| `RATE_LIMITED` | Rate limit exceeded |
| `UNAUTHORIZED` | Invalid or missing API key |

## SDK Usage

```typescript
import { createClient } from '@fresh/sdk';

const client = createClient({ apiKey: 'your-api-key' });

// Basic search
const result = await client.search('hottest AI startups', {
  numResults: 10
});

result.results.forEach(item => {
  console.log(item.title);
  console.log(item.url);
});

// Deep research search
const deep = await client.search('AI regulations impact', {
  type: 'deep',
  numResults: 20,
  highlights: { query: 'policy compliance', maxCharacters: 300 }
});

// Deep reasoning with synthesis
const reasoning = await client.search('best strategy for AI adoption', {
  type: 'deep-reasoning',
  numResults: 10
});

if (reasoning.output) {
  console.log(reasoning.output.content);
  reasoning.output.grounding.forEach(g => {
    console.log(`Confidence: ${g.confidence}`);
    g.citations.forEach(c => console.log(`  - ${c.title}: ${c.url}`));
  });
}
```

## Pricing

Exa search pricing (separate from fetch):

- **Base cost:** Included in soft dollar system
- **Deep reasoning:** Higher cost per query due to synthesis
- See [Exa.ai pricing](https://exa.ai/pricing) for details

